That&#x27;s quite an old fashioned way of testing exceptions, TestNG has allowed you to do the following since 2005:<p><pre><code>    @Test(expectedExceptions = FooBarException.class)
    public void test() {
      thisShouldThrow();
    }
</code></pre>
If the method doesn&#x27;t throw or throws the wrong kind of exception, this test will fail.

With Junit, just write<p><pre><code>  @Test(expected = FooBarException.class)
  void testFooBarException() {
      thisShouldThrowFooBarException()
  }</code></pre>
